@lsm5 Yes, c/image is being updated; then we can update c/image in Skopeo, and that will include this dependency update.

Note that _right now_ c/image is building fine; x/exp is also a dependency of c/image, and the update of x/exp in c/image is correctly failing CI, see the above-linked PR.

So I don’t think that extending c/image’s CI to catch this situation is necessary — but of course, extending c/image’s CI might very well be valuable anyway. (In particular, I think nothing would notice if we started depending on a Go version not shipped in relevant operating systems.)
